Rating: 4
After reading some of the reviews, I altered the recipe a bit. I used 1 medium sweet onion, thin sliced; 2 cloves garlic, minced; 1/2 yellow pepper, sliced; 1 T chili powder, 1/2 t cumin, 1/4 t cayenne pepper, 3/4 lb ground turkey; 1 14.5-oz can Mexican stewed tomatoes, 1 8-oz can tomato sauce, 1 c fresh corn. Serve on thin multi-grain spagetti and garnish with black beans and shredded medium cheddar. Just enough for my family of four. This recipe was a huge hit and I will definitely make it again.

