I took the advice of the other reviewers, and doubled the spices (except the caynne, I like hot but not smokin'), it was the right thing to do, I didn't feel it was too spiceful with the extra. I had in my freezer, blanched soy beans, I threw in about a cup or so and it added another meaty texture, plus they're really good for you. I also used whole wheat pasta, so this dish was pretty darn healthy and tasty! I used crushed tomatoes, (I've found that there is a greater ratio of tomato to juice in the can). And I simmered it all until it was more dry then wet, so it wasn't too soupy. Make extra, it's holds up well and is great the next day.

