Rating: 4
I have been making this dish for years, probably once a month since it was first published in 1991. I always substitute penne for rigatoni just becuase we like smaller pasta, and recently I made two other changes that I think make a big difference, so I'd like to share them. I increase the spices as other cooks have suggested, and now I add an 8-oz. can of tomato sauce in addition to the canned tomatoes. This makes the sauce MUCH richer. I also increae the simmering time to about 20 minutes. I also suggest adding the chopped cilantro at the very end. Otherwise, it gets cooked down and less flavorful. This is a wonderful weeknight dish and I'm sure it will continue to a staple in my repetoire.

